 school and that of Anglophone philosophers of history of the 1960s and 1970s. "This work, in my view, puts the whole problem of narrative, not to mention philosophy of history, on a new and higher plane of discussion."-Hayden White, History and Theory "Superb. . . . A fine point of entrance into the work of one of the eminent thinkers of the present intellectual age."-Joseph R. Gusfield, Contemporary Sociology  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 0aHistoryxPhilosophy. 0aMimesis in literature. 0aNarration (Rhetoric). 0aPlots (Drama, novel, etc.). 0aTime in literature. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aMcLaughlin, Kathleen.1 aPellauer, David.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package Archive 1960-1989z978311066784440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226713519423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226713519.jpg  a978-3-11-066784-4  UChP eBook-Package Archive 1960-1989c1960d1989  aGBV-deGruyter-alles